WEBVTT

00:13.066 --> 00:16.000
[bright tone]

00:16.066 --> 00:19.000
[tense jazzy music]

00:19.066 --> 00:26.100
♪ ♪

01:47.266 --> 01:48.734
- 'Twas the night
before Christmas,

01:48.800 --> 01:51.834
and all through the house,
not a creature was stirring,

01:51.900 --> 01:53.700
not even a mouse.

01:53.767 --> 01:56.400
The rats, on the other hand,

01:56.467 --> 01:59.033
is a whole different story.

01:59.100 --> 02:01.367
[tense percussive tone]

02:01.433 --> 02:04.967
- [praying indistinctly]

02:05.033 --> 02:06.500
- Hey, Said,

02:06.567 --> 02:08.900
I got a little gift
for you here.

02:09.867 --> 02:15.033
♪ ♪

02:15.100 --> 02:16.333
- Okay, what do we got?

02:16.400 --> 02:18.767
- I was bitten by a rat.

02:18.834 --> 02:20.233
- Jesus.

02:20.300 --> 02:23.133
Can you take that?

02:23.200 --> 02:25.667
[sighs]
Lie back.

02:25.734 --> 02:26.900
- Christmas Eve.

02:26.967 --> 02:28.767
[door buzzes]
- Yeah.

02:28.834 --> 02:31.533
I think it's snowing.

02:31.600 --> 02:35.500
- When I was a boy, this
was the best night of all.

02:35.567 --> 02:40.567
Our house was full of music,
lights, food, cousins.

02:40.633 --> 02:41.900
Em City is so empty.

02:41.967 --> 02:43.100
- Sure, it is.

02:43.166 --> 02:44.567
We're in the middle
of a lockdown

02:44.633 --> 02:47.767
'cause the Aryans
attacked the Muslims.

02:47.834 --> 02:49.734
- I'm getting a premonition
like I used to

02:49.800 --> 02:52.600
when God would talk to me.

02:52.667 --> 02:54.133
- God would talk to you?

02:54.200 --> 02:56.734
- He would tell me what
was going to happen.

02:56.800 --> 03:00.500
- And is he talking
to you now?

03:00.567 --> 03:01.600
So, what's he saying?

03:02.600 --> 03:07.000
- He says, "be afraid."

03:08.266 --> 03:12.667
- Eugene, Miguel asked
you a question.

03:12.734 --> 03:14.200
Can you forgive him?

03:17.300 --> 03:19.433
- [Miguel moaning]

03:19.500 --> 03:20.467
- No!

03:20.533 --> 03:24.233
No! No! No! No!

03:24.300 --> 03:26.600
♪ ♪

03:34.767 --> 03:37.100
- Miguel...

03:40.867 --> 03:43.467
I, uh--

03:43.533 --> 03:47.367
I talked to Eugene
and Tina yesterday,

03:47.433 --> 03:50.300
and, um,

03:50.367 --> 03:52.033
they've decided...

03:52.100 --> 03:54.767
they don't want to continue
with the program.

03:54.834 --> 03:58.000
- Oh.

03:58.066 --> 03:59.400
Too bad.

04:00.300 --> 04:03.333
You know, I had a lot of things
that I wanted to say to him.

04:03.400 --> 04:06.300
- Well,

04:06.367 --> 04:07.433
you could say them to me.

04:07.500 --> 04:10.467
- Not the same thing.

04:10.533 --> 04:13.233
- Of course not.
I understand.

04:13.300 --> 04:14.967
There are certain things
you should only say

04:15.033 --> 04:18.333
to certain people...

04:18.400 --> 04:20.367
Like...

04:20.433 --> 04:23.166
the warden.

04:23.233 --> 04:26.467
He's expecting you to tell him
who raped his daughter.

04:29.533 --> 04:31.900
- [chuckles]

04:31.967 --> 04:33.500
- Are you prepared
to do that?

04:34.300 --> 04:35.533
- No.

04:35.600 --> 04:39.467
- Miguel, do you want to
go back to Solitary?

04:39.533 --> 04:41.200
- No.

04:45.700 --> 04:49.033
- Then my advice is...

04:49.100 --> 04:51.300
that you take this day,

04:51.367 --> 04:53.467
pray to God,

04:53.533 --> 04:57.033
look within

04:57.100 --> 04:59.033
and make a choice.

05:01.667 --> 05:04.400
- May Almighty God bless you,
in the name of the Father,

05:04.467 --> 05:06.734
the Son,
and the Holy Spirit.

05:06.800 --> 05:08.200
The mass has ended.

05:08.266 --> 05:10.633
Go in peace to love
and serve the Lord.

05:10.700 --> 05:13.333
Alleluia, Alleluia.

05:13.400 --> 05:15.967
[together]
Thanks be to God, Alleluia.

05:16.033 --> 05:17.734
- Merry Christmas, everybody.

05:17.800 --> 05:19.734
[together]
Merry Christmas, Father.

05:24.166 --> 05:27.400
[indistinct chatter]

05:27.467 --> 05:29.166
- Yo, hermano,

05:29.233 --> 05:30.967
I hear Glynn
is letting Hernandez,

05:31.033 --> 05:33.066
Guerra, and Ricardo
back into Emerald City.

05:33.133 --> 05:34.166
- Yeah.

05:34.233 --> 05:36.100
- If I was you,
I'd watch my ass.

05:36.166 --> 05:37.600
- Why is that?

05:37.667 --> 05:40.166
- I saw how when they got
busted, you walked away.

05:40.233 --> 05:42.700
That's not too cool, bro,
deserting your amigos like that.

05:42.767 --> 05:44.300
- Why don't you leave
me the fuck alone?

05:44.367 --> 05:46.900
- Hernandez is gonna be
in a nasty-ass mood,

05:46.967 --> 05:48.500
looking to take it out
on someone.

05:48.567 --> 05:49.600
That's all I'm saying.

05:52.066 --> 05:53.533
- My sister'll be here
to see me.

05:53.600 --> 05:54.767
- Are you sure?

05:54.834 --> 05:56.900
- Yeah, she knows how much
I love Christmas.

05:58.133 --> 06:01.166
[door buzzes]

06:08.734 --> 06:11.533
- Miguelito,
feliz navidad!

06:11.600 --> 06:13.567
- Where'd you
disappear to, man?

06:13.633 --> 06:15.066
- What do you mean,
disappear?

06:15.133 --> 06:17.900
- All four of us are together,
only three of us are cuffed.

06:17.967 --> 06:21.066
- Come on, guys, back up.

06:21.133 --> 06:23.834
You got to forgive them,
Miguelito.

06:23.900 --> 06:25.533
They had a lot of time
to themselves

06:25.600 --> 06:28.000
to wonder about things.

06:28.066 --> 06:31.667
But me,
I don't wonder.

06:31.734 --> 06:33.800
I know.

06:33.867 --> 06:36.633
You're not one of us.

06:36.700 --> 06:39.233
You never will be.

06:39.300 --> 06:41.066
[tapping on door]

06:41.133 --> 06:43.000
- Why is it I get nervous seeing
the four of you

06:43.066 --> 06:44.533
huddled in this pod together?

06:44.600 --> 06:45.567
Huh?

06:45.633 --> 06:46.567
Whoever don't live here,
come on.

06:46.633 --> 06:48.633
Vamoose.

06:48.700 --> 06:50.133
Let's go.

06:53.000 --> 06:57.100
Hernandez, for Christ's sake,
it's Christmas, huh?

06:57.166 --> 06:59.800
Take a break from
being a tough guy.

07:03.400 --> 07:07.400
- He's right.

07:07.467 --> 07:09.433
Enjoy the day.

07:09.500 --> 07:12.533
[eerie tones]

07:15.166 --> 07:17.200
It'll be your last.

07:22.867 --> 07:25.867
- I made up my mind.

07:25.934 --> 07:27.033
I'm not gonna tell
the warden anything

07:27.100 --> 07:31.133
about his daughter's rape.

07:31.200 --> 07:33.100
- Are you sure
about this?

07:33.166 --> 07:36.000
Have you really
thought it through?

07:39.066 --> 07:40.300
- Yeah.

07:40.367 --> 07:42.800
I want to go
back to Solitary.

07:45.300 --> 07:47.233
- Okay, I'll make
the arrangements,

07:47.300 --> 07:49.033
transfer you out of here
first thing tomorrow.

07:49.100 --> 07:50.166
- No, not tomorrow.

07:50.233 --> 07:51.367
I want to go right now.

07:51.433 --> 07:53.033
- Transfers take time.
- Fuck that.

07:53.100 --> 07:55.100
I want to go right now.
- Why, Miguel?

07:55.166 --> 07:56.967
Are you in danger?

07:57.033 --> 08:00.900
Because if you are, we can
put you in protective custody.

08:00.967 --> 08:03.367
- What difference does
it make, you know?

08:03.433 --> 08:05.000
Alone is alone.

08:05.066 --> 08:07.834
That's the way I've been
my whole fucking life.

08:07.900 --> 08:11.233
I just don't belong
in the world.

08:11.300 --> 08:16.100
I belong by myself.

08:16.166 --> 08:18.367
Solitary.

08:23.567 --> 08:24.934
- Whoa, whoa. Is she coming?

08:25.000 --> 08:27.266
- She's not on the list.

08:27.333 --> 08:29.667
- Well, check it again.

08:29.734 --> 08:31.500
- Ricardo,
I double-checked it.

08:31.567 --> 08:34.000
Your sister didn't
schedule a visit.

08:34.066 --> 08:36.367
Nobody in your family did.

08:36.433 --> 08:39.467
[tense percussive tones]

08:43.800 --> 08:46.533
- Carlo, it's time.

09:04.667 --> 09:06.533
- You leaving us,
Alvarez?

09:06.600 --> 09:09.000
- Before you go, we want
to give you something.

09:10.233 --> 09:13.433
♪ ♪

09:13.500 --> 09:14.800
[groans]

09:14.867 --> 09:16.000
- Fuck.

09:16.066 --> 09:18.200
- My first day I got here,
I got stuck.

09:18.266 --> 09:20.166
No more,
you fucking cocksucker.

09:20.233 --> 09:21.200
- Drop it!

09:21.266 --> 09:25.367
I said drop it!

09:25.433 --> 09:27.133
Get out.

09:30.734 --> 09:32.266
- Ricardo's dead.

09:32.333 --> 09:33.433
- Lockdown!

09:33.500 --> 09:34.433
[doors buzz]

09:34.500 --> 09:36.266
Let's go, come on.

09:36.333 --> 09:37.867
Move it.

09:37.934 --> 09:39.834
[alarm blaring]

09:39.900 --> 09:42.934
- Season's greetings,
fuckwad.

09:43.000 --> 09:46.033
[door slams shut]

10:00.467 --> 10:02.700
- Well, Alvarez is
back in solitary.

10:02.767 --> 10:06.066
I guess the circle
is complete.

10:06.133 --> 10:09.667
- Ray,
I am so sorry.

10:09.734 --> 10:12.033
- Sorry?

10:12.100 --> 10:14.066
Is this an official
confession?

10:14.133 --> 10:17.000
- I should never
have excluded you.

10:17.567 --> 10:19.700
Maybe if you had attended
the sessions with Alvarez

10:19.767 --> 10:22.600
and Rivera, things might
have ended up differently.

10:22.667 --> 10:24.400
- I doubt it.

10:26.367 --> 10:28.266
Well, there goes
the baby Jesus,

10:28.333 --> 10:32.000
back in the box
for another year.

10:32.066 --> 10:34.300
And the wise men,

10:34.367 --> 10:35.767
Larry, Curly and Moe.

10:36.266 --> 10:39.100
- [laughs]

10:39.166 --> 10:42.033
- Pete,
have you absolutely decided

10:42.100 --> 10:43.633
to stop being a nun?

10:44.567 --> 10:47.600
- Well, you know,
the process of getting out

10:47.667 --> 10:50.333
is just as hard as getting in,

10:50.400 --> 10:53.867
so by the time I'm done,
who knows?

10:53.934 --> 10:57.033
- I admire your courage.

10:57.100 --> 11:00.467
- Sometimes, it takes
just as much courage

11:00.533 --> 11:02.333
to stay as to go.

11:03.100 --> 11:04.834
- Maybe,

11:04.900 --> 11:07.367
but if the magi
had stayed in Persia,

11:07.433 --> 11:11.500
did what they were supposed
to do, followed all the rules,

11:11.567 --> 11:12.900
they never would
have seen God.

11:16.767 --> 11:17.867
- Thank you.

11:21.667 --> 11:24.266
- I got word at home
that you wanted to see me,

11:24.333 --> 11:26.166
that you wanted to talk
about Ardeth's attacker.

11:27.000 --> 11:30.834
- So you want to know
who raped her, right?

11:34.100 --> 11:36.600
- Yes.

11:36.667 --> 11:39.767
- Why?

11:39.834 --> 11:42.333
- So they can be punished.

11:42.400 --> 11:45.567
- What if I told you
that the one who did it

11:45.633 --> 11:47.033
has already been
punished?

11:47.100 --> 11:48.033
- The name.

11:48.100 --> 11:51.467
I want the name.

11:51.533 --> 11:53.900
- Carlo Ricardo.

11:55.934 --> 11:58.367
[tense percussive music]

11:58.433 --> 12:02.333
He's been here
the whole time.

12:02.400 --> 12:05.433
[laughing]

12:13.700 --> 12:16.767
[continues laughing]

12:30.567 --> 12:33.934
- I'm sorry about
your brother.

12:34.000 --> 12:35.467
- Did you know him?

12:35.533 --> 12:38.533
- No.

12:38.600 --> 12:43.834
- Carlo could
never rest.

12:43.900 --> 12:46.500
Maybe finally now...

12:46.567 --> 12:49.400
[sobs]
He'll get some.

12:52.533 --> 12:56.033
- ♪ God rest
ye merry gentlemen ♪

12:56.100 --> 12:58.166
♪ Let nothing you dismay ♪

12:59.800 --> 13:03.800
♪ Remember Christ the savior ♪

13:03.867 --> 13:05.934
♪ Was born on Christmas day ♪

13:07.266 --> 13:11.400
♪ To save us all
from Satan's power ♪

13:11.467 --> 13:14.867
♪ When we were gone astray ♪

13:14.934 --> 13:20.533
♪ Oh, tidings of
comfort and joy ♪

13:20.600 --> 13:22.867
♪ Comfort and joy ♪

13:22.934 --> 13:29.600
♪ Oh, tidings of
comfort and joy ♪

13:32.867 --> 13:35.200
- I was supposed to die
this Thursday,

13:35.266 --> 13:37.934
the last execution
of the millennium.

13:38.000 --> 13:39.900
But the governor heard
that I'm pregnant,

13:39.967 --> 13:44.633
and an hour ago,
he issued a temporary stay.

13:44.700 --> 13:46.834
- Well, knowing Devlin,

13:46.900 --> 13:49.600
he's, uh, just trying
to sort through

13:49.667 --> 13:53.166
the political ramifications
of putting to death a woman

13:53.233 --> 13:57.400
who got pregnant
while in prison.

13:57.467 --> 13:59.300
You--you do know
who the father is?

13:59.367 --> 14:00.433
- Why, yes. Of course.

14:00.500 --> 14:01.433
- But you won't tell?

14:01.500 --> 14:02.934
- No.

14:03.000 --> 14:05.600
- The list is easy
to pare down.

14:05.667 --> 14:09.333
- The father doesn't matter.

14:09.400 --> 14:11.367
I want you
to go to the governor

14:11.433 --> 14:14.567
and tell him to go forward
with the execution.

14:17.233 --> 14:19.133
- Y-you want to die?

14:19.200 --> 14:21.734
- I have to die.

14:21.800 --> 14:23.000
- Why?

14:23.066 --> 14:27.667
- I did kill my first born.

14:27.734 --> 14:29.767
Oh, I've said it.

14:31.934 --> 14:34.100
Some things aren't real
till you say them out loud.

14:36.533 --> 14:38.567
- I know.

14:39.700 --> 14:44.100
- My daughter,
my precious.

14:44.166 --> 14:47.133
When she was born,
she was a joy,

14:47.200 --> 14:49.867
but bit by bit, I began to see
that there was something

14:49.934 --> 14:52.433
not quite right
about her,

14:52.500 --> 14:57.467
something
not quite human...

14:57.533 --> 14:58.834
Otherworldly.

15:01.100 --> 15:02.900
I'd go into her room

15:02.967 --> 15:06.600
and above the bassinet,
there'd be flashes of fire.

15:06.667 --> 15:07.867
- Fire?

15:07.934 --> 15:10.100
- Or she'd speak
in tongues.

15:10.166 --> 15:13.800
One day, she even made
a plate levitate.

15:13.867 --> 15:15.600
That's when I began to see

15:15.667 --> 15:18.300
she was possessed
of the Devil.

15:20.066 --> 15:22.233
- Did you, um,

15:22.300 --> 15:23.834
ever talk to anyone
about this?

15:23.900 --> 15:25.867
- Who could I tell?

15:25.934 --> 15:27.700
My mother?

15:27.767 --> 15:31.200
The child's father,
that lying bastard?

15:31.266 --> 15:34.233
- Uh, well, your minister,

15:34.300 --> 15:35.567
pediatrician.

15:35.633 --> 15:39.500
- They would have thought
I was crazy.

15:39.567 --> 15:41.600
No, I knew the only way
was to kill her myself.

15:43.767 --> 15:47.300
But every time I went to strike,
I didn't see the devil.

15:48.500 --> 15:50.934
I only saw my daughter's
sweet face.

15:53.934 --> 15:56.633
So I put her in the car

15:56.700 --> 15:58.600
and drove into the lake

15:58.667 --> 16:00.500
and let her drown,

16:00.567 --> 16:03.633
half hoping, half expecting
to see her rise up

16:03.700 --> 16:06.500
out of the water
on Lucifer's back.

16:08.133 --> 16:11.500
- Hmm.

16:11.567 --> 16:14.000
All right.

16:14.066 --> 16:15.300
I'll see what I can do.

16:15.367 --> 16:19.300
Oh, God bless you.

16:19.367 --> 16:20.834
- In three hours,
I'm hosting a party

16:20.900 --> 16:23.100
at the mansion
for close to 400 people.

16:23.166 --> 16:25.600
Now, what's all this
about Shirley Bellinger?

16:25.667 --> 16:27.633
- She wants to
be executed.

16:27.700 --> 16:29.066
- Well, good.

16:29.133 --> 16:30.834
That solves
all my problems.

16:30.900 --> 16:32.433
A little something
extra under the tree.

16:32.500 --> 16:35.567
- Excuse me, Governor,
but there's one hitch.

16:35.633 --> 16:37.333
She's insane.

16:37.400 --> 16:39.700
- She drowned her daughter.
We knew that.

16:39.767 --> 16:43.000
- The woman does not belong
on death row.

16:43.066 --> 16:44.633
She should be in
the state asylum.

16:44.700 --> 16:47.500
- But if she wants to die,

16:47.567 --> 16:49.266
who are we to stand in her way?

16:49.333 --> 16:52.834
- Governor, she is not fit
to make that decision.

16:52.900 --> 16:56.233
She is certifiable
and she is pregnant,

16:56.300 --> 17:00.100
and if you execute her,
you will be committing murder.

17:00.166 --> 17:03.300
Two murders.

17:03.367 --> 17:05.333
- Transfer Bellinger.

17:05.400 --> 17:06.767
And, Warden,

17:06.834 --> 17:08.800
I want you to end
this lockdown.

17:08.867 --> 17:10.333
- We don't have the situation
under control.

17:10.400 --> 17:12.834
- It's Christmas and I'm
getting heat from the clergy,

17:12.900 --> 17:16.367
including the Cardinal,
who will be at my party tonight.

17:16.433 --> 17:19.300
Let the inmates out!

17:20.834 --> 17:23.867
And so, in the spirit of
this blessed holiday season,

17:23.934 --> 17:28.000
I commute Shirley Bellinger's
sentence to life imprisonment

17:28.066 --> 17:30.700
without the possibility
of parole.

17:30.767 --> 17:34.233
This action in no way affects
my long-standing support

17:34.300 --> 17:37.800
for the death penalty.

17:37.867 --> 17:40.000
- You betrayed me.

17:40.066 --> 17:42.500
- I protected you,
and your baby.

17:42.567 --> 17:45.500
- I want an abortion, and if
you all won't give me one,

17:45.567 --> 17:48.133
I will kill this monster
inside me myself.

17:48.200 --> 17:50.033
- You are being sent to
the Connelly Institute,

17:50.100 --> 17:52.000
where you will be on
24-hour watch.

17:52.066 --> 17:54.467
- You're making a mistake!

17:54.533 --> 17:56.800
Mark my words,
next year at this time,

17:56.867 --> 17:58.500
you won't be
celebrating Christmas.

17:58.567 --> 18:00.900
You'll be bowing
down before Satan.

18:00.967 --> 18:03.533
The next millennium
belongs to him.

18:03.600 --> 18:07.700
Satan is the father,
and I'm the virgin mother!

18:07.767 --> 18:11.700
[tense music]

18:11.767 --> 18:15.266
- There's only one thing that's
gonna make this all okay...

18:15.333 --> 18:16.333
You, dead.

18:16.400 --> 18:18.133
[both grunting]

18:18.200 --> 18:19.333
- No!

18:19.400 --> 18:22.567
[indistinct shouting
and grunting]

18:48.367 --> 18:51.500
[bell ringing]

18:51.567 --> 18:54.500
[tense percussive music]

18:54.567 --> 19:01.633
♪ ♪

19:21.333 --> 19:23.100
- Hey.

19:23.166 --> 19:27.233
- Hey.

19:27.300 --> 19:28.934
- You're back.

19:29.000 --> 19:31.000
- Yeah, so are you.

19:31.066 --> 19:32.367
- Yeah.

19:34.800 --> 19:37.033
Feeling better?

19:37.100 --> 19:40.000
- I'm alive,

19:40.066 --> 19:41.734
thanks to you.

19:45.533 --> 19:48.734
Keller...

19:48.800 --> 19:51.934
I just asked McManus to let
you be my roommate again.

20:07.967 --> 20:09.767
- Oh, boy,

20:09.834 --> 20:11.367
Schillinger's home.

20:14.100 --> 20:16.934
- He's not such
a bad guy, Diane.

20:17.000 --> 20:19.667
- What drugs
are you on?

20:19.734 --> 20:22.133
- He's a shitload
better than them.

