I will quit.

52:45.967 --> 52:47.367
- You afraid, Murph?

52:47.433 --> 52:50.700
- Yeah, sure.
- Yeah, me, too.

52:50.767 --> 52:52.400
- Leo?

52:52.467 --> 52:56.633
- Yeah?

52:56.700 --> 52:59.967
- We can't hide behind
the badge anymore.

53:00.033 --> 53:01.333
- What do you mean?

53:01.400 --> 53:04.133
- All these years,
you've been in the system.

53:04.200 --> 53:06.066
All these years,
you've worked for them,

53:06.133 --> 53:08.333
caging in your own kind.

53:08.400 --> 53:09.667
Don't you ever feel sometimes
like you've betrayed

53:09.734 --> 53:11.300
your own people?

53:11.367 --> 53:12.934
- No.

53:13.000 --> 53:15.367
- No?

53:15.433 --> 53:17.567
- [sighs]

53:17.633 --> 53:22.000
The men who are locked in here,
they're not my people.

53:22.066 --> 53:28.166
My people are the ones
who obey the law.

53:28.233 --> 53:30.367
Go home, Clayton.

53:30.433 --> 53:31.500
You're fired.

53:32.166 --> 53:39.200
♪ ♪

53:42.300 --> 53:44.433
- There's lots of folks who
think the world's gonna end

53:44.500 --> 53:46.734
come the dawn of
this new millennium.

53:46.800 --> 53:49.467
They think we'll see
the second coming of Christ,

53:49.533 --> 53:52.433
the Apocalypse,
Armageddon, doomsday.

53:52.500 --> 53:55.200
They've tied it all
to God's great plan.

53:55.266 --> 53:58.867
But ask yourself, does
God know it's January 1st?

53:58.934 --> 54:00.700
Does he have his watch
set for midnight?

54:00.767 --> 54:04.300
And if he does,
which time zone is he in?

54:04.367 --> 54:08.133
Man invented hours,
days, and minutes.

54:08.200 --> 54:10.767
Man invented
calendars and clocks.

54:10.834 --> 54:13.567
God's got his own timetable,
and it's stupid for us to think

54:13.633 --> 54:14.967
that we can set it for him.

54:15.033 --> 54:18.567
All we can do is
watch the clock run out

54:18.633 --> 54:20.200
and hope for the best.

54:22.800 --> 54:25.734
[buzzer sounds]

54:25.800 --> 54:27.767
- Happy New Year.

54:29.900 --> 54:34.166
- Yeah.

54:34.233 --> 54:40.266
♪ ♪

54:40.333 --> 54:43.633
- Happy New Year.

54:43.700 --> 54:45.166
- Happy New Year.

54:48.834 --> 54:51.266
- [speaking Russian]

54:53.333 --> 54:55.200
- Happy New Years,
motherfucker.

54:55.266 --> 54:57.133
- Eat me, you little prick.

54:57.200 --> 55:00.400
♪ ♪

55:00.467 --> 55:03.500
- [grunting]

55:08.867 --> 55:10.967
- Happy New Years,
little brother.

55:16.567 --> 55:19.600
[monitors beeping]

55:53.400 --> 55:56.433
[reciting prayers quietly]

56:08.767 --> 56:14.367
[dramatic tones]

56:14.433 --> 56:21.467
♪ ♪

56:45.767 --> 56:48.333
- A bunch of men sit in cells

56:48.400 --> 56:50.867
on the brink of a new year,

56:50.934 --> 56:52.767
a new century,

56:52.834 --> 56:55.400
a new millennium,

56:55.467 --> 56:57.600
1,000 years.

56:57.667 --> 57:00.100
They stare into the future,

57:00.166 --> 57:03.133
and all they see is themselves

57:03.200 --> 57:04.333
in those same cells.

57:07.233 --> 57:10.467
Black or white, here we are,

57:10.533 --> 57:11.567
on the precipice.

57:12.800 --> 57:16.266
We either hang on
or we fall off,

57:16.333 --> 57:18.000
together or separately.

57:19.500 --> 57:21.300
It's our choice.

57:21.367 --> 57:22.700
It's up to us.

57:23.266 --> 57:26.400
It's up to you and me.

57:27.500 --> 57:29.100
[noisemaker blows]

57:29.166 --> 57:31.300
Happy New Year!
